WEBVTT

00:06.074 --> 00:08.209
announcer:
IN THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM,

00:08.242 --> 00:12.080
SEXUALLY BASED OFFENSES ARE
CONSIDERED ESPECIALLY HEINOUS.

00:12.113 --> 00:14.215
IN NEW YORK CITY,
THE DEDICATED DETECTIVES

00:14.248 --> 00:15.816
WHO INVESTIGATE
THESE VICIOUS FELONIES

00:15.849 --> 00:17.251
ARE MEMBERS
OF AN ELITE SQUAD

00:17.285 --> 00:19.387
KNOWN AS
THE SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT.

00:19.420 --> 00:22.156
THESE ARE THEIR STORIES.

00:24.625 --> 00:27.561
[playing classical music]

00:27.595 --> 00:39.307
*

00:39.340 --> 00:42.476
[Spanish pop music on radio]

00:42.510 --> 00:50.218
*

00:50.251 --> 00:51.519
- $2.78 CHANGE.
- GRACIAS.

00:51.552 --> 00:54.555
HAVE A NICE DAY.

01:04.165 --> 01:05.233
THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

01:12.273 --> 01:15.276
- HOLD THE DOOR?

01:17.311 --> 01:19.547
GOOD CATCH.
- NO PROBLEM.

01:22.483 --> 01:25.119
- YOU LOOK HAPPY.

01:25.153 --> 01:26.487
- SURE, WHY NOT?

01:30.391 --> 01:33.394
THANKS.

01:56.817 --> 01:59.820
- DON'T SCREAM.

02:02.890 --> 02:05.893
GO.

02:10.264 --> 02:13.267
SIT.

02:15.303 --> 02:19.307
- I'M SARAH.

02:19.340 --> 02:21.875
CAN I GET YOU
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

02:21.909 --> 02:24.278
- YOU GOT A BEER?

02:24.312 --> 02:27.315
- YEAH,
I THINK SO.

03:03.484 --> 03:05.953
[cell phone ringing]
- OH, THAT'S MY BOYFRIEND.

03:05.986 --> 03:09.923
HE MIGHT BE COMING OVER--
- LEAVE IT.

03:09.957 --> 03:12.960
GO ON.

03:20.268 --> 03:21.535
[ringing stops]

03:31.011 --> 03:31.879
YOU A MUSICIAN?

03:31.912 --> 03:34.615
- YES, I COULD PLAY
SOMETHING FOR YOU.

03:34.648 --> 03:36.284
I HAVE A TEST LATER.
I SHOULD--

03:36.317 --> 03:39.320
- NO.

03:41.322 --> 03:43.257
- MONEY.

03:43.291 --> 03:44.892
I ONLY HAVE
A FEW DOLLARS OF CASH,

03:44.925 --> 03:45.893
BUT WE COULD GO
TO AN ATM--

03:45.926 --> 03:48.929
- I DON'T NEED
YOUR MONEY.

03:50.864 --> 03:53.867
- PLEASE DON'T
KILL ME.

03:56.036 --> 03:58.272
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

03:58.306 --> 04:01.375
- TAKE OFF
YOUR CLOTHES.

04:04.312 --> 04:05.279
IN THERE.

04:05.313 --> 04:08.416
- OKAY.

04:08.449 --> 04:12.353
BUT YOU DON'T NEED
YOUR GUN.

04:12.386 --> 04:15.389
I WILL DO ANYTHING
THAT YOU WANT ME TO.

04:17.491 --> 04:20.494
[gun sets on table]

04:25.433 --> 04:28.436
- TAKE OFF
YOUR CLOTHES.

04:38.379 --> 04:41.382
LAY DOWN.

04:57.998 --> 05:01.068
[groans]

05:03.637 --> 05:06.073
- SARAH?

05:06.106 --> 05:09.843
SARAH?

05:09.877 --> 05:10.944
WHAT TIME WAS THAT?

05:10.978 --> 05:14.081
- UM, AROUND 1:00.

05:14.114 --> 05:15.649
- THIS MORNING?

05:15.683 --> 05:18.419
- UH,
YESTERDAY AFTERNOON.

05:20.120 --> 05:22.456
- OH, OKAY.

05:22.490 --> 05:25.058
UM...

05:25.092 --> 05:28.596
CAN YOU TELL ME WHY
YOU WAITED SO LONG TO REPORT?

05:28.629 --> 05:30.498
- I HAD A JURY
AT 4:00.

05:30.531 --> 05:33.501
IT'S LIKE A RECITAL
THAT GETS GRADED.

05:33.534 --> 05:36.537
AND IF I DIDN'T GO,
I'D GET--

05:39.407 --> 05:42.576
I DIDN'T YELL.

05:42.610 --> 05:45.579
I DIDN'T
FIGHT BACK.

05:45.613 --> 05:47.114
I MEAN,
I DIDN'T KNOW IF--

05:47.147 --> 05:49.483
- SARAH, YOU SAID
THAT HE HAD A GUN.

05:49.517 --> 05:51.552
IT WAS RAPE.

05:51.585 --> 05:53.053
YOU'RE ALIVE.

05:53.086 --> 05:56.089
YOU DID WHAT
YOU HAD TO DO.

06:00.127 --> 06:03.163
[dramatic music]

06:03.196 --> 06:10.370
*

06:47.475 --> 06:48.375
- SHE'S JUST A KID.
WHAT HAPPENED?

06:48.408 --> 06:50.911
- SOPHOMORE AT MANHATTAN ACADEMY
OF MUSIC.

06:50.944 --> 06:53.847
SHE WAS RAPED AT GUNPOINT
IN HER APARTMENT YESTERDAY.

06:53.881 --> 06:55.015
- WAS THERE ANY OUTCRY?

06:55.048 --> 06:57.585
- SHE SHOWERED RIGHT AFTER
AND WENT TO A PIANO RECITAL.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.920
- AND YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
SHE'S TOLD?

06:59.953 --> 07:02.490
- GREAT. YOU AND AMARO
CAN TAKE HER FOR A RAPE KIT.

07:02.523 --> 07:04.224
- WELL, ACTUALLY, I'M STILL
GETTING HER TO TRUST ME.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.860
- OKAY, KEEP IT SMALL.

07:06.894 --> 07:09.897
- I'LL SEND ROLLINS AND FIN
TO THE APARTMENT WITH C.S.U.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.499
THINK YOU CAN GET
HIS DNA?

07:11.532 --> 07:13.066
- HE USED A CONDOM
AND FLUSHED IT.

07:13.100 --> 07:15.435
- GOOD LUCK.

07:17.705 --> 07:18.972
- ALMOST DONE.

07:19.006 --> 07:20.474
NEXT, I'LL USE
A SPECIAL INSTRUMENT

07:20.508 --> 07:22.576
THAT CAN TAKE PHOTOS
OF ANY TRAUMA.

07:22.610 --> 07:24.545
- NOW, SARAH, YOU SAID
THAT YOU GAVE HIM A BEER?

07:24.578 --> 07:26.480
- IT'S ON
MY COFFEE TABLE.

07:26.514 --> 07:28.482
I HAVEN'T MOVED IT.
IT'S IN A PLASTIC CUP.

07:28.516 --> 07:31.051
I THOUGHT THAT
THAT MIGHT BE BETTER FOR DNA.

07:31.084 --> 07:33.086
- ACTUALLY, THE BOTTLE
WOULD'VE BEEN BETTER.

07:33.120 --> 07:36.256
- I'LL REMEMBER THAT
FOR NEXT TIME.

07:36.289 --> 07:40.227
- I'M SORRY.
I-I WASN'T THINKING.

07:40.260 --> 07:42.930
- YEAH, IT'S FINE.

07:42.963 --> 07:44.131
- HI, SARAH?

07:44.164 --> 07:45.666
I'M JEN, YOUR CRISIS COUNSELOR.

07:45.699 --> 07:47.200
- WHOA, YOU CAN'T
JUST BARGE IN HERE.

07:47.234 --> 07:50.871
- I'M HERE TO HELP.
- CAN YOU MOVE TOWARD ME?

07:50.904 --> 07:55.275
I'M SORRY, BUT YOU'RE
GONNA FEEL A LITTLE PRESSURE.

07:55.308 --> 07:57.144
- OKAY.
[camera clicking]

07:57.177 --> 08:00.180
GRAB THAT CUP
OFF THE TABLE.

08:02.716 --> 08:05.719
- LET'S GO AHEAD AND CUT
A SAMPLE FROM THE MATTRESS.

08:08.922 --> 08:11.925
[clears throat]

08:13.293 --> 08:16.597
- THIS IS THE LAST TUBE.
- YOU'RE DOING GREAT, SARAH.

08:16.630 --> 08:17.665
- SARAH, AS YOUR ADVOCATE,

08:17.698 --> 08:18.966
I WANNA MAKE YOU AWARE THAT

08:18.999 --> 08:20.601
ONE OF YOUR OPTIONS
IS TO NOT FILE CHARGES--

08:20.634 --> 08:22.135
- EXCUSE ME?
- YOU SHOWERED.

08:22.169 --> 08:24.538
THERE'S A LACK
OF OBVIOUS PHYSICAL VIOLENCE.

08:24.572 --> 08:26.306
THOSE CASES CAN BE
DIFFICULT TO PROSECUTE.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.175
- THEY ALSO GIVE YOU
A VOICE TO SAY

08:28.208 --> 08:30.277
THAT THIS IS NOT OKAY
AND TO DEMAND JUSTICE.

08:30.310 --> 08:32.880
- PROSECUTION IS
EMOTIONALLY GRUELING--

08:32.913 --> 08:34.281
- JEN, CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND OUTSIDE?

08:34.314 --> 08:37.517
THANK YOU.

08:39.086 --> 08:40.053
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:40.087 --> 08:41.589
- IT'S MY JOB TO ENSURE

08:41.622 --> 08:44.324
THE SURVIVOR KNOWS EVERYTHING
ABOUT THIS PROCESS.

08:44.357 --> 08:45.325
I DON'T SUGARCOAT.

08:45.358 --> 08:47.661
- AND YOU'VE BEEN A COUNSELOR
FOR HOW LONG?

08:47.695 --> 08:49.963
- YEAH, YOU'VE BEEN DOING
THIS LONGER.

08:49.997 --> 08:51.198
BUT I HAVE
FRESHER EYES.

08:51.231 --> 08:53.100
THE REALITY IS
THE SYSTEM DOESN'T ALWAYS WORK.

08:53.133 --> 08:56.003
- I UNDERSTAND THAT, BUT
THAT GIRL HAS JUST BEEN ROBBED

08:56.036 --> 08:58.872
OF ALL HER POWER
AND ALL HER HUMANITY.

08:58.906 --> 09:00.273
AND YOUR BEST ADVICE IS

09:00.307 --> 09:02.275
PRETEND IT NEVER HAPPENED
AND WALK AWAY?

09:02.309 --> 09:04.678
- THAT'S NOT--I MEANT--

09:04.712 --> 09:07.715
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

09:12.252 --> 09:13.621
[sighs]

09:13.654 --> 09:14.988
JEN SAYS TO CALL HER
IF YOU WANT.

09:15.022 --> 09:16.223
- THANK YOU.

09:16.256 --> 09:19.326
- THESE REDUCE YOUR RISK
OF S.T.D.s AND HIV.

09:19.359 --> 09:20.894
THIS WILL PREVENT PREGNANCY.

09:20.928 --> 09:24.264
YOUR CHOICE.

09:24.297 --> 09:25.966
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:25.999 --> 09:29.002
HEPATITIS B SHOTS.

09:32.205 --> 09:36.343
- YOU OKAY?

09:36.376 --> 09:39.279
SARAH, YOU'RE NOT ALONE.

09:39.312 --> 09:41.081
I WILL BE HERE

09:41.114 --> 09:44.117
EVERY STEP OF THE WAY.

10:00.267 --> 10:02.035
- THEY DON'T CLEAN UP
WHEN THEY'RE DONE?

10:02.069 --> 10:03.303
- [whispers]
YEAH.

10:03.336 --> 10:06.406
SARAH, IS THERE ANYPLACE ELSE
THAT YOU MIGHT BE ABLE TO STAY?

10:06.439 --> 10:09.309
YOUR PARENTS OR...

10:09.342 --> 10:10.878
- NO, NOT A GOOD IDEA.

10:10.911 --> 10:13.146
THEY WERE AGAINST ME
MOVING OUT OF THE DORMS,

10:13.180 --> 10:15.282
ESPECIALLY INTO
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD.

10:15.315 --> 10:16.950
- [whispers]
OKAY.

10:16.984 --> 10:21.321
THIS IS A HUGE BURDEN TO BEAR,
IN MY EXPERIENCE.

10:21.354 --> 10:23.290
- IN YOUR EXPERIENCE?

10:23.323 --> 10:25.926
UNTIL YOU'VE BEEN RAPED,

10:25.959 --> 10:28.962
YOU DON'T GET--

10:31.932 --> 10:33.333
I'M SORRY.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.669
I-I'M ON EDGE.

10:35.703 --> 10:37.905
I NEED SOME TIME.

10:37.938 --> 10:39.306
- LOOK,
YOU HAVE MY NUMBER.

10:39.339 --> 10:43.210
CALL ME?

10:43.243 --> 10:45.713
SARAH?
- [gasps]

10:45.746 --> 10:49.316
SORRY.

10:49.349 --> 10:50.317
- CALL ME.

10:50.350 --> 10:53.220
- THANKS.

10:53.253 --> 10:56.256
I'LL BE FINE.

11:03.363 --> 11:06.266
[sniffs]

11:06.299 --> 11:09.302
[whimpers]

11:18.946 --> 11:21.314
- [sighs]

11:21.348 --> 11:23.183
- LOW-GRADE IMAGE.
AND THE TIME CODE'S ALL WONKY.

11:23.216 --> 11:25.052
- LOOK FOR TWOS.
WHITE GIRL, BLACK GUY.

11:25.085 --> 11:28.121
SHE'S CARRYING GROCERIES.

11:28.155 --> 11:32.125
THERE, THAT'S HER.
SLOW IT DOWN.

11:32.159 --> 11:34.327
- SEEMS LIKE HE'S BEEN
ON THAT ELEVATOR BEFORE.

11:34.361 --> 11:38.031
- HE KNOWS WHERE THE CAMERA IS.

11:38.065 --> 11:39.199
- THEY'RE ALMOST FRIENDLY.

11:39.232 --> 11:40.500
- SHE SAID
SHE'S NEVER SEEN HIM BEFORE.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.502
- THAT'S WHY I HATE ELEVATORS,
YOU KNOW?

11:42.535 --> 11:44.237
NO--NO GIRL'S GONNA SMILE
AT SOME STRANGER

11:44.271 --> 11:45.472
WHO TRIES TO GET
INTO HER CAR.

11:45.505 --> 11:47.274
- ALL RIGHT,
GET A SCREEN GRAB.

11:47.307 --> 11:49.910
START SWEEPING
THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

11:49.943 --> 11:50.911
[knock at door]

11:50.944 --> 11:52.445
- [gasps]
- SARAH?

11:52.479 --> 11:54.214
YOU THERE?
IT'S ME.

11:54.247 --> 11:55.715
- [sighs]

12:04.357 --> 12:06.493
- HEY, BABE.

12:06.526 --> 12:08.195
Y-YOU STILL UP
FOR CELEBRATING?

12:08.228 --> 12:11.364
- NOT A GOOD TIME.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.166
RAIN CHECK?

12:13.200 --> 12:14.334
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

12:14.367 --> 12:17.270
- UM...UH...
UH, BEDBUGS.

12:17.304 --> 12:18.105
- OH.

12:18.138 --> 12:20.941
- THE EXTERMINATOR
WAS JUST...HERE.

12:20.974 --> 12:21.942
- I WOULD OFFER TO HELP,
BUT--

12:21.975 --> 12:23.043
- I KNOW.

12:23.076 --> 12:26.079
IT'S--IT'S OKAY.
I GET IT.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.063
[subway clatters]

12:46.499 --> 12:49.336
- HIM?

12:49.369 --> 12:51.104
- MAYBE. YEAH.

12:51.138 --> 12:52.439
HEY!
HEY.

12:52.472 --> 12:53.473
N.Y.P.D.
YOU, UP AGAINST THE WALL.

12:53.506 --> 12:55.175
- WHAT?
- YOU!

12:55.208 --> 12:57.310
- SHUT UP. DO WHAT SHE SAYS.
YOU KNOW THE DRILL.

12:57.344 --> 12:59.312
- IS HE YOUR PROTECTION?

12:59.346 --> 13:00.981
- TURN AROUND.
NOW.

13:01.014 --> 13:03.016
- COME ON, MAN.
LIKE, SERIOUSLY, BRO?

13:03.050 --> 13:06.019
- YEAH, SERIOUSLY.
WHY DON'T Y'ALL GRAB SOME TOO?

13:06.053 --> 13:09.056
- HERE YOU GO,
SWEETIE.

13:30.243 --> 13:31.311
- UM--
OH!

13:31.344 --> 13:33.280
GOD, I'M SORRY.
UM--

13:33.313 --> 13:34.381
- NO PROBLEM.

13:34.414 --> 13:37.417
IT'S OKAY.

13:39.352 --> 13:42.055
- HE WAS
JUST OUTSIDE,

13:42.089 --> 13:44.524
HANGING OUT,
AND HE SMILED AT ME.

13:44.557 --> 13:46.293
- HE HEADED NORTH
HOW LONG AGO?

13:46.326 --> 13:48.061
- FIVE MINUTES?

13:48.095 --> 13:50.363
- JEFFERSON PROJECTS
ARE JUST UP AMSTERDAM.

13:50.397 --> 13:53.300
LOOK, SARAH,
KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.302
[police radio chatter]

13:57.370 --> 14:01.942
- [gasps]

14:01.975 --> 14:04.211
THERE, THAT'S HIM!
- YOU SURE?

14:04.244 --> 14:07.247
- I THINK SO.

14:10.417 --> 14:12.319
- YO, MY MAN!

14:12.352 --> 14:14.387
HEY. CONVERSATION W--
HEY, HEY!

14:14.421 --> 14:17.357
WHOA, STOP!
POLICE!

14:17.390 --> 14:18.926
HEY!

14:18.959 --> 14:21.962
HEY!

14:31.504 --> 14:33.173
- MICHAEL?

14:33.206 --> 14:34.474
HEY! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:34.507 --> 14:36.343
- GET DOWN!
- GET OFF ME!

14:36.376 --> 14:38.011
- N.Y.P.D.!
- GET OFF HIM!

14:38.045 --> 14:39.179
- WHAT WAS THAT?
WAS THAT A GUN?

14:39.212 --> 14:40.547
- LEAVE MY BOY ALONE!
- DON'T MOVE!

14:40.580 --> 14:41.982
- YOU CAN'T COME UP
IN HERE!

14:42.015 --> 14:42.983
- SHUT UP.
- BACK UP.

14:43.016 --> 14:44.017
- GET OUT
OF MY HOUSE!

14:44.051 --> 14:45.452
- I SAID, SHUT UP!

14:45.485 --> 14:48.188
- THIS IS MY BABY!
DON'T HURT HIM!

14:48.221 --> 14:50.357
- EVERYONE SHUT UP!
NOW STEP BACK. NOW.

14:50.390 --> 14:51.524
- ALL THIS
FOR SOME WEED?

14:51.558 --> 14:53.393
IT'S NOT EVEN
A FELONY AMOUNT!

14:53.426 --> 14:55.328
- [grunts] THAT WEED'S THE LEAST
OF YOUR PROBLEMS.

14:55.362 --> 14:59.332
- [crying] DON'T TAKE HIM!
HE DIDN'T DO NOTHING!

14:59.366 --> 15:01.201
- I'M GOING TO
DRIVE BY,

15:01.234 --> 15:04.237
YOU TELL ME IF YOU SEE
THE MAN THAT RAPED YOU.

15:08.308 --> 15:09.276
- THAT'S HIM.

15:09.309 --> 15:11.378
- ARE YOU SURE?
- ABSOLUTELY.

15:11.411 --> 15:13.146
ALL RIGHT,
TAKE THE SON OF A BITCH IN.

15:13.180 --> 15:16.183
- COPY THAT.

15:25.158 --> 15:26.126
- WHAT HAPPENED
TO MS. CABOT?

15:26.159 --> 15:27.294
- CALLED AWAY,
YOUR HONOR.

15:27.327 --> 15:28.295
ROSE CALLIER,
FOR THE PEOPLE.

15:28.328 --> 15:29.997
- STATEMENT?
- YOUR HONOR,

15:30.030 --> 15:31.564
THE DEFENDANT
FORCIBLY RAPED SARAH WALSH

15:31.598 --> 15:33.300
AT GUNPOINT
IN HER APARTMENT.

15:33.333 --> 15:35.368
HE HAS NO JOB
OTHER THAN DEALING DRUGS.

15:35.402 --> 15:37.504
THE PEOPLE SUGGEST BAIL
BE SET AT $50,000.

15:37.537 --> 15:38.405
- RESPONSE?

15:38.438 --> 15:41.474
- YOUR HONOR,
MY CLIENT, TOM O'BRIEN--

15:41.508 --> 15:43.977
- HIS NAME IS MICHAEL!
- WHAT?

15:44.011 --> 15:47.314
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
- MICHAEL. WEDMORE.

15:47.347 --> 15:48.315
- RIGHT.

15:48.348 --> 15:49.549
SORRY,
YOUR HONOR.

15:49.582 --> 15:52.152
UH, THIS ONE JUST, EH--

15:52.185 --> 15:53.286
- ARE YOU SERIOUS?

15:53.320 --> 15:55.222
- ORDER IN THE COURT!
SIT DOWN.

15:55.255 --> 15:57.524
COUNSELOR, YOU NEED TIME
TO GET YOUR CASE ORGANIZED?

15:57.557 --> 15:59.326
- JUST A SECOND,
YOUR HONOR.

15:59.359 --> 16:02.562
- [whispers] YOU GOTTA ASK
FOR A NEW LAWYER.

16:02.595 --> 16:04.497
- JUDGE, CAN I
GET A NEW LAWYER?

16:04.531 --> 16:07.500
- MR. WEDMORE, YOU ARE ENTITLED
TO A COURT-APPOINTED ATTORNEY.

16:07.534 --> 16:10.303
YOU ARE NOT ENTITLED
TO YOUR CHOICE OF ATTORNEY.

16:10.337 --> 16:12.239
CAN YOU AFFORD TO
HIRE A LAWYER?

16:12.272 --> 16:14.074
- WE HAVE A LAWYER,
YOUR HONOR.

16:14.107 --> 16:15.308
- MOM?

16:15.342 --> 16:17.344
- BAYARD ELLIS?

16:17.377 --> 16:19.546
COUNSELOR, TO WHAT
DO WE OWE THIS PRIVILEGE?

16:19.579 --> 16:22.382
- I'M HERE TO REPRESENT
MICHAEL WEDMORE...PRO BONO.

16:22.415 --> 16:24.484
- YOUR HONOR--
- IF IT PLEASES THE COURT.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.254
- THIS SUITABLE TO YOU,
MR. WEDMORE?

16:27.287 --> 16:28.355
- YEAH.

16:28.388 --> 16:31.291
- SO ORDERED.

16:31.324 --> 16:32.492
- WILL HE GET OUT
ON BAIL?

16:32.525 --> 16:34.061
- BAIL'S SET
AT $50,000.

16:34.094 --> 16:37.530
THAT SHOULD HOLD HIM.

16:37.564 --> 16:38.798
HEY, MIKE.

16:38.831 --> 16:40.800
SARAH, THIS IS
BUREAU CHIEF MIKE CUTTER.

16:40.833 --> 16:43.170
HE'S GONNA BE
THE LEAD PROSECUTOR ON THE CASE.

16:43.203 --> 16:45.338
- SARAH.
- BUREAU CHIEF?

16:45.372 --> 16:46.506
IS THIS BECAUSE
OF BAYARD ELLIS?

16:46.539 --> 16:48.108
WHY IS HE TAKING
THE CASE?

16:48.141 --> 16:49.776
- OH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT HIM.

16:49.809 --> 16:52.212
JUST MEANS THAT WE HAVE TO
VET EVERY DETAIL.

16:52.245 --> 16:56.516
PLEASE,
TAKE A SEAT.

16:56.549 --> 16:57.817
[door closes]

16:57.850 --> 17:02.455
SO LET'S START
WITH THE SECURITY TAPE.

17:02.489 --> 17:04.791
NOW, THE, UH,
THE ASSAILANT ENTERED

17:04.824 --> 17:06.459
THE ELEVATOR
WITH YOU.

17:06.493 --> 17:09.496
CAN I ASK WHY YOU
HELD THE DOOR FOR HIM?

17:09.529 --> 17:11.298
- I JUST--

17:11.331 --> 17:13.133
I DIDN'T WANT HIM TO THINK
I WAS A RACIST.

17:13.166 --> 17:17.270
- OKAY.
THAT'S...FINE.

17:17.304 --> 17:18.238
NOW...

17:18.271 --> 17:22.109
ON THE TAPE,
YOU APPEAR TO BE TALKING TO HIM.

17:22.142 --> 17:24.544
- HEY, NEW GUY.
GOOD WORK LAST NIGHT.

17:24.577 --> 17:26.779
- OH,
JUST GOT LUCKY.

17:26.813 --> 17:27.747
THIS DUMB KID
DIDN'T KNOW

17:27.780 --> 17:29.582
BETTER THAN TO WORK
HIS OWN NEIGHBORHOOD.

17:29.616 --> 17:30.850
- CAN'T BE THAT DUMB.

17:30.883 --> 17:32.419
HE'S GOT BAYARD ELLIS
DEFENDING HIM.

17:32.452 --> 17:33.353
- WHA--WHO'S THAT?

17:33.386 --> 17:36.123
- HE'S THE GO-TO LAWYER
FOR DRUG KINGPINS.

17:36.156 --> 17:37.857
- USED TO BE
UNTIL ABOUT SIX YEARS AGO.

17:37.890 --> 17:41.261
HE WON A HUGE CIVIL SUIT,
WALKED AWAY, TOOK THE MONEY,

17:41.294 --> 17:43.430
AND STARTED THE NEW YORK CENTER
FOR CIVIL LIBERTIES.

17:43.463 --> 17:45.365
- TRYING TO BUY
A CLEAN CONSCIENCE.

17:45.398 --> 17:48.268
ASK ME, HE'S STILL JUST PUTTING
CRIMINALS BACK ON THE STREET.

17:48.301 --> 17:50.303
- ONLY IF WE DON'T
DO OUR JOB.

17:50.337 --> 17:52.372
ANY FUNNY BUSINESS
LAST NIGHT?

17:52.405 --> 17:53.306
GOOD.
OKAY.

17:53.340 --> 17:54.774
SO GO FIND OUT WHAT
HE'S GOING TO FIND OUT

17:54.807 --> 17:57.177
BEFORE HE FINDS IT OUT.

17:57.210 --> 17:59.512
- AFTER YOU SHOWERED,
DID YOU CALL ANYONE?

17:59.546 --> 18:02.415
YOUR BOYFRIEND?
- NO.

18:02.449 --> 18:05.485
- BUT YOU HAVE ONE?

18:05.518 --> 18:08.488
- YES.
- HIS NAME?

18:08.521 --> 18:09.856
- SARAH?

18:09.889 --> 18:14.394
WE'RE GONNA NEED
TO TALK TO HIM.

18:14.427 --> 18:15.862
- UH, I DIDN'T TELL HIM.

18:15.895 --> 18:19.532
I DIDN'T WANT HIM
INVOLVED.

18:19.566 --> 18:21.534
HE'S MY PIANO TEACHER
AT THE SCHOOL.

18:21.568 --> 18:24.571
HE COULD LOSE
HIS JOB.

18:28.408 --> 18:29.409
- HAS SHE HAD
A PERFORMANCE?

18:29.442 --> 18:30.377
- UH, YEAH.

18:30.410 --> 18:33.846
SARAH HAD A JURY PERFORMANCE
TWO DAYS AGO.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.782
SHE WAS AMAZING.

18:35.815 --> 18:39.186
- OH, WAS THAT DIFFERENT
THAN NORMAL?

18:39.219 --> 18:40.853
- YOU KNOW, MUSICIANS
ARE A LOT LIKE BOXERS.

18:40.887 --> 18:42.555
THEY TEND TO EXCEL
MORE QUICKLY

18:42.589 --> 18:45.158
IF THEY'RE
FROM HARDER BACKGROUNDS.

18:45.192 --> 18:46.393
SHE'S FROM LONG ISLAND.

18:46.426 --> 18:47.360
- HUH.

18:47.394 --> 18:52.432
NOW, DID YOU NOTICE
ANYTHING OFF ABOUT HER?

18:52.465 --> 18:55.468
- SHE JUST ACCEPTED HER PRAISE
AND HUSTLED OUT.

18:55.502 --> 18:58.938
PLAYING THAT HARD CAN BE
EMOTIONALLY DRAINING.

18:58.971 --> 19:00.373
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

19:02.475 --> 19:04.544
- SARAH?

19:04.577 --> 19:06.813
SARAH.

19:06.846 --> 19:10.250
- WHAT? UH, SORRY,
WH--UM...

19:10.283 --> 19:11.318
WHAT DID YOU ASK?

19:11.351 --> 19:14.521
- THE LAST TIME YOU HAD SEX
BEFORE THE INCIDENT.

19:14.554 --> 19:18.458
- UH, TWO WEEKS AGO.

19:18.491 --> 19:19.926
I'VE BEEN FOCUSING
ON MY MUSIC.

19:19.959 --> 19:21.528
[knock at door]

19:21.561 --> 19:23.530
- LIV, CAN I SPEAK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

19:23.563 --> 19:26.566
- EXCUSE ME.

19:29.469 --> 19:30.937
WHAT'S UP?

19:30.970 --> 19:33.440
- WE WENT BACK TO THE BAR
WHERE SARAH SPOTTED HER PERP.

19:33.473 --> 19:35.575
TURNS OUT SHE WAS THERE
THE NIGHT BEFORE.

19:35.608 --> 19:37.277
- YEAH, I KNOW. SHE TOLD ME.
SHE HAS A FAKE I.D.

19:37.310 --> 19:38.478
SHE HAD A BEER.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.413
- WELL, IT SOUNDS LIKE
SHE WAS HITTING IT

19:40.447 --> 19:41.581
A LITTLE BIT HARDER
THAN THAT.

19:41.614 --> 19:43.483
SHE WAS PLAYING
AIR KEYBOARDS,

19:43.516 --> 19:46.419
SINGING ALONG
TO PIANO MAN.

19:46.453 --> 19:48.488
- OKAY.
ANYTHING ELSE?

19:48.521 --> 19:51.458
[knock at door]

19:51.491 --> 19:52.492
- EVERYTHING OKAY?

19:52.525 --> 19:56.796
- SO, SARAH,
YOUR BARTENDER SAYS

19:56.829 --> 19:58.298
THAT HE SAW
YOU DRUNK

19:58.331 --> 19:59.966
AND FLIRTING
WITH A GUY

19:59.999 --> 20:02.535
THE NIGHT BEFORE
YOU WERE ATTACKED.

20:02.569 --> 20:04.337
WAS THAT
YOUR BOYFRIEND?

20:04.371 --> 20:05.838
- NO.

20:05.872 --> 20:08.241
IT WAS JUST SOME GUY
AT THE BAR.

20:08.275 --> 20:10.410
I WAS STRESSED ABOUT, UH,
THE RECITAL.

20:10.443 --> 20:12.279
- DID YOU GO HOME
WITH THIS GUY?

20:12.312 --> 20:15.415
- NO.

20:15.448 --> 20:17.817
AND I DON'T LIKE BEING TREATED
LIKE I DID SOMETHING WRONG.

20:17.850 --> 20:19.452
- WELL, NOBODY'S JUDGING YOU,
HONEY.

20:19.486 --> 20:22.489
- WE JUST CAN'T AFFORD
ANY SURPRISES.

20:26.626 --> 20:29.529
- YOU WANNA TELL ME WHAT'S
GOING ON WITH THAT DETECTIVE?

20:29.562 --> 20:31.398
- UM...NO.

20:31.431 --> 20:33.500
- [sighs]
WHAT THE HELL--

20:33.533 --> 20:35.468
YOU'VE BEEN SECRETIVE,
DISTANT.

20:35.502 --> 20:36.403
ARE YOU SEEING
SOMEONE?

20:36.436 --> 20:40.273
- NO, PAUL.

20:40.307 --> 20:45.044
[sighs]
I WAS RAPED.

20:45.077 --> 20:49.482
IN MY APARTMENT
TUESDAY.

20:49.516 --> 20:53.320
- OH, GOD.

20:53.353 --> 20:55.555
- I MEAN, AT LEAST
I'M PLAYING BETTER, RIGHT?

20:55.588 --> 20:58.591
- I-I-I'M SO SORRY.

21:03.396 --> 21:05.832
I-I WAS THE ONE WHO TOLD YOU
TO MOVE THERE.

21:05.865 --> 21:10.036
- [scoffs]
THIS ISN'T ABOUT YOU.

21:10.069 --> 21:11.371
AT ALL!

21:11.404 --> 21:14.441
- SARAH.

21:14.474 --> 21:18.478
- COUNSELOR ELLIS.

21:18.511 --> 21:21.814
- HAVE WE MET?
- SERGEANT JOHN MUNCH.

21:21.848 --> 21:23.450
I ADMIRE
YOUR SECOND ACT.

21:23.483 --> 21:25.918
- UM, I'M NOT SURE
I GET THE JOKE.

21:25.952 --> 21:27.487
- I'M NOT JOKING.

21:27.520 --> 21:30.490
YOU CAN BE N.Y.P.D.
AND BELIEVE IN CIVIL LIBERTIES.

21:30.523 --> 21:32.559
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

21:32.592 --> 21:33.626
- I'M ABOUT TO PUT THAT
TO THE TEST.

21:33.660 --> 21:35.061
- OKAY.

21:35.094 --> 21:38.565
- UH, MR. ELLIS IS HERE
ON BEHALF OF MICHAEL WEDMORE.

21:38.598 --> 21:40.032
- THE, UH,
ELEVATOR SURVEILLANCE TAPE.

21:40.066 --> 21:41.033
I'LL NEED A COPY
OF THAT.

21:41.067 --> 21:43.336
ALSO THE U.F. 250s
FROM THE STOP AND FRISKS.

21:43.370 --> 21:44.537
- WAIT, WHAT?

21:44.571 --> 21:45.838
- UH,
DETECTIVE,

21:45.872 --> 21:47.574
TWO NIGHTS AGO,
SEVERAL YOUNG BLACK MEN

21:47.607 --> 21:49.342
IN HAMILTON HEIGHTS
WERE STOPPED AND FRISKED

21:49.376 --> 21:51.611
BY A BLONDE FEMALE
AND BLACK MALE DETECTIVE TEAM.

21:51.644 --> 21:53.946
THAT WOULD BE YOU AND, UH--
- DETECTIVE TUTUOLA.

21:53.980 --> 21:55.948
WE WERE LOOKING
FOR A RAPIST AT LARGE.

21:55.982 --> 21:58.084
- YOU CAN TELL
SOMEONE'S A RAPIST

21:58.117 --> 22:00.520
BY STOPPING
AND FRISKING THEM?

22:00.553 --> 22:02.855
I'LL NEED A REPORT
ON EACH INDIVIDUAL STOPPED.

22:02.889 --> 22:05.525
- ROLLINS, FIN,
TAKE COUNSELOR ELLIS

22:05.558 --> 22:06.325
INTO THE INTERVIEW ROOM,

22:06.359 --> 22:07.860
AND BRING HIM
WHATEVER HE NEEDS.

22:07.894 --> 22:09.061
- RIGHT THIS WAY,
COUNSELOR.

22:09.095 --> 22:11.531
- IT MAY TAKE A WHILE FOR US
TO GET THE REPORTS IN ORDER.

22:11.564 --> 22:13.500
- I'M NOT WORRIED.
YOUR PARTNER HERE...

22:13.533 --> 22:16.536
I'M SURE
SHE KEEPS GOOD NOTES.

22:19.472 --> 22:22.509
- YOU THINK A GUY LIKE THAT
REALLY FOUND RELIGION?

22:22.542 --> 22:25.111
- THERE'S NOT A LOT OF MONEY IN
RAPE...OR THE FOURTH AMENDMENT.

22:25.144 --> 22:28.381
- SPEAKING OF WHICH,
TELL ME ABOUT THE GUN BUST.

22:28.415 --> 22:29.516
- IT'S CLEAN.

22:29.549 --> 22:32.585
I'VE WORKED NARCOTICS, WARRANTS.
DONE HUNDREDS OF THESE.

22:32.619 --> 22:35.855
- AND I'VE SEEN HUNDREDS OF
DROPSY CASES GET THROWN OUT.

22:35.888 --> 22:38.425
- WHAT, ARE YOU TRYING
TO SAY SOMETHING, COUNSELOR?

22:38.458 --> 22:40.393
- I'M ASKING THE QUESTION.

22:40.427 --> 22:43.830
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

22:43.863 --> 22:46.499
- DETECTIVE SECOND GRADE
NICHOLAS AMARO.

22:46.533 --> 22:48.501
HE THREW THE GUN
UNDER THE COUCH.

22:48.535 --> 22:50.036
I RETRIEVED IT.

22:50.069 --> 22:51.971
NOW, I'M NOT SURE
IF THE GIRL WAS RAPED.

22:52.004 --> 22:54.841
BUT I DO KNOW
THERE WAS A GUN.

22:54.874 --> 22:57.043
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
WE'RE ALL ON THE SAME TEAM HERE.

22:57.076 --> 22:58.545
PUT 'EM AWAY.

22:58.578 --> 23:00.447
- IT'S NOT PERSONAL,
DETECTIVE.

23:00.480 --> 23:01.347
ELLIS WINS THIS CASE,

23:01.380 --> 23:03.950
IT'S NOT JUST OPEN SEASON
ON MY OFFICE

23:03.983 --> 23:06.118
BUT ALSO N.Y.P.D.

23:06.152 --> 23:08.688
OKAY?

23:18.230 --> 23:19.566
- HEY, OLIVIA.

23:19.599 --> 23:20.967
IT'S NICK.

23:23.603 --> 23:24.437
- HEY.

23:24.471 --> 23:27.106
- HEY. UH,
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU--

23:27.139 --> 23:29.576
I'M--I'M NOT, UH--
- NO. NO, NOT AT ALL.

23:29.609 --> 23:30.843
COME IN.

23:30.877 --> 23:32.011
- THANKS.
- YEAH.

23:35.648 --> 23:38.050
- THIS IS A NICE SPOT.
- UH, YEAH.

23:38.084 --> 23:39.619
THANK YOU.

23:41.220 --> 23:44.190
ARE YOU OKAY? WHAT'S UP?

23:44.223 --> 23:46.192
- YOU KNOW THIS, UH, CUTTER?

23:46.225 --> 23:47.860
WHAT'S YOUR TAKE ON HIM?

23:47.894 --> 23:50.563
- CUTTER, HE'S A GOOD LAWYER.
HE'S DEDICATED.

23:50.597 --> 23:52.599
- TO HIS BATTING AVERAGE
OR THE TEAM?

23:52.632 --> 23:55.502
- OH, NO. HE'S ON OUR SIDE.

23:55.535 --> 23:57.837
BUT HE KNOWS THAT WE ARE...

23:57.870 --> 23:59.438
IN FOR A BATTLE.

24:01.974 --> 24:06.579
- ARE WE CLEAR
ON WHAT HAPPENED WITH THE GUN?

24:06.613 --> 24:08.481
- YEAH. YOU YELLED, "GUN,"
AND I DREW ON HIM.

24:08.515 --> 24:11.117
- YEAH, BUT YOU SAW HIM
THROW IT, RIGHT?

24:11.150 --> 24:13.886
- NO, YOU DID.
I GOT THERE AFTER.

24:13.920 --> 24:15.254
[cell phone rings]

24:15.287 --> 24:16.556
- IT'S CUTTER.

24:16.589 --> 24:18.525
LOOK, AMARO,
WE'RE GONNA BE FINE.

24:18.558 --> 24:19.626
WE'RE GONNA BE FINE.

24:19.659 --> 24:22.028
- [sighs]

24:22.061 --> 24:25.064
- BENSON.

24:27.066 --> 24:29.869
YOU GOTTA BE
KIDDING ME.

24:29.902 --> 24:32.204
[cell phone rings]

24:32.238 --> 24:33.906
- HELLO?

24:33.940 --> 24:35.875
automated voice: HELLO. I'M
CALLING FROM THE VINE SERVICE.

24:35.908 --> 24:38.277
YOU'RE REGISTERED TO RECEIVE
UPDATES ABOUT AN OFFENDER.

24:38.310 --> 24:41.581
LAST NAME, WEDMORE.
FIRST NAME, MICHAEL.

24:41.614 --> 24:43.282
I'M CALLING TO TELL YOU
THAT THERE HAS BEEN A CHANGE

24:43.315 --> 24:46.018
IN THIS OFFENDER'S
CUSTODY STATUS.

24:46.052 --> 24:48.855
THIS OFFENDER HAS BEEN RELEASED
FROM CUSTODY.

24:48.888 --> 24:51.190
IF YOU HAVE ANY CONCERNS
ABOUT YOUR IMMEDIATE SAFETY,

24:51.223 --> 24:53.593
CONTACT YOUR LOCAL
LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY.

24:53.626 --> 24:57.263
OF, IF YOU HAVE AN EMERGENCY,
CALL 911.

24:57.296 --> 25:01.300
FOR MORE INFORMATION, CONTACT
RIKERS ISLAND IN BRONX COUNTY.

25:01.333 --> 25:03.135
- ELLIS POSTED MICHAEL'S BAIL,

25:03.169 --> 25:05.071
BUT I DON'T WANT YOU
TO WORRY ABOUT IT.

25:05.104 --> 25:06.873
- HE KNOWS
WHERE I LIVE.

25:06.906 --> 25:08.541
- THERE'S A PENDING
RESTRAINING ORDER,

25:08.575 --> 25:10.943
AND I'M SENDING A UNIT
OVER TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

25:10.977 --> 25:12.311
- NO, I HAVE TO GO.
- SARAH.

25:12.344 --> 25:15.548
SARAH.
[call ends]

25:19.919 --> 25:21.888
- HEY.

25:54.320 --> 25:56.623
- I'M SO GLAD
YOU CAME.

25:56.656 --> 25:58.024
YOU KNOW YOUR FATHER
AND I LOVE IT

25:58.057 --> 25:59.626
WHEN YOU STAY WITH US
AT THE HOUSE.

25:59.659 --> 26:04.263
WE MISS
OUR LITTLE GIRL.

26:04.296 --> 26:06.599
SARAH.
HONEY?

26:06.633 --> 26:09.135
- UM, I'M--
I HAVE TO GO.

26:09.168 --> 26:12.171
I'M L--
I'M LATE FOR PRACTICE.

26:20.647 --> 26:22.882
- I HEARD WEDMORE
POSTED BAIL.

26:22.915 --> 26:23.916
HOW'S YOUR GIRL?

26:23.950 --> 26:25.217
- SHE WANTS TO GO
AT IT ALONE.

26:25.251 --> 26:27.286
SHE DOESN'T WANT
ANYONE TO KNOW.

26:27.319 --> 26:29.055
- WHAT IS SHE, 20?
- 19.

26:29.088 --> 26:30.122
- GOD.

26:30.156 --> 26:31.924
REMEMBER WHEN YOU THOUGHT
YOU WERE STRONG ENOUGH,

26:31.958 --> 26:35.327
YOU COULD HANDLE ANYTHING
BY YOURSELF?

26:35.361 --> 26:36.663
WHAT'S UP, SERGEANT?

26:36.696 --> 26:38.297
- ELLIS IS DOING
HIS DUE DILIGENCE.

26:38.330 --> 26:39.365
- AND THEN SOME.

26:39.398 --> 26:40.633
HE'S MOVED
FOR A MAPP HEARING

26:40.667 --> 26:42.234
ON THE RECOVERY
OF THE GUN.

26:42.268 --> 26:44.403
YOU'LL BOTH NEED TO TESTIFY.
- WELL, I'M READY.

26:44.436 --> 26:46.072
- HE'S ALSO MOVED
FOR A WADE HEARING,

26:46.105 --> 26:47.940
CHALLENGING THE FAIRNESS
OF THE I.D.

26:47.974 --> 26:50.677
- THAT WOULD BE YOU TWO AGAIN,
AS WELL AS FIN AND ROLLINS.

26:50.710 --> 26:51.678
YOU CAN CARPOOL.

26:51.711 --> 26:53.680
- THAT WAS
GOOD POLICE WORK.

26:53.713 --> 26:54.947
WHAT'S THIS GUY
TRYING TO DO?

26:54.981 --> 26:58.651
- DEATH BY
A THOUSAND PAPER CUTS.

26:58.685 --> 27:01.654
[playing dramatic
classical music]

27:01.688 --> 27:08.928
*

27:12.064 --> 27:13.165
[hitting sour notes]

27:13.199 --> 27:14.901
[music stops]

27:14.934 --> 27:16.268
- [sighs]

27:16.302 --> 27:18.404
- WE CONDUCTED
A SHOW-UP IDENTIFICATION

27:18.437 --> 27:21.708
WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME OF
THE VICTIM SEEING THE SUSPECT.

27:21.741 --> 27:24.043
IT'S STANDARD
N.Y.P.D. PROCEDURE.

27:24.076 --> 27:25.678
- WHY DIDN'T YOU BRING
MR. WEDMORE IN FOR A LINE-UP?

27:25.712 --> 27:26.979
- YOUR HONOR,
THE COURT

27:27.013 --> 27:29.982
HAS UPHELD SHOW-UP IDs
TIME AND TIME AGAIN.

27:30.016 --> 27:31.083
- MY CLIENT
WAS I.D.'D

27:31.117 --> 27:32.985
WHILE HANDCUFFED AND
STANDING WITH THE DETECTIVES.

27:33.019 --> 27:34.120
IT'S INHERENTLY
SUGGESTIVE.

27:34.153 --> 27:38.958
- THE VICTIM WAS HELD BY
HER RAPIST FOR ALMOST AN HOUR.

27:38.991 --> 27:42.194
SHE HAS GOOD EYESIGHT.
IT'S A CLEAN I.D.

27:42.228 --> 27:43.896
- YOUR HONOR, THE NEW JERSEY
STATE SUPREME COURT

27:43.930 --> 27:46.432
HAS ACKNOWLEDGED
A TROUBLING LACK OF RELIABILITY

27:46.465 --> 27:48.367
IN EYEWITNESS
IDENTIFICATIONS,

27:48.400 --> 27:50.402
PARTICULARLY THOSE INVOLVING
A DIFFERENCE IN RACE.

27:50.436 --> 27:52.371
- THIS IS NOT
NEW JERSEY.

27:52.404 --> 27:54.306
I'M GOING TO AGREE
WITH THE PROSECUTION.

27:54.340 --> 27:57.343
MOTION DENIED,
THE IDENTIFICATION STANDS.

27:59.411 --> 28:02.381
[playing classical music]

28:02.414 --> 28:09.121
*

28:15.061 --> 28:17.363
- HE CONTINUED
INTO THE JEFFERSON PROJECTS,

28:17.396 --> 28:19.498
RAN UP THE STAIRS
INTO HIS APARTMENT,

28:19.531 --> 28:22.434
HE TRIED TO SLAM
THE DOOR ON ME.

28:22.468 --> 28:24.136
THEN I TOOK HIM DOWN.

28:24.170 --> 28:25.504
- DID YOU SEE HIM
THROW THE GUN?

28:25.537 --> 28:27.239
- I SAW HIM
FLING HIS ARM,

28:27.273 --> 28:28.240
AND I HEARD IT SLIDE
ACROSS THE FLOOR.

28:28.274 --> 28:29.909
- YOU HEARD IT?

28:29.942 --> 28:32.144
WITH THE CHILD CRYING,
MR. WEDMORE'S FAMILY SCREAMING?

28:32.178 --> 28:36.182
- YES, AND I SAW IT
GO UNDER THE COUCH.

28:36.215 --> 28:39.051
- DID YOU KNOW IT WAS A GUN,
OR THINK IT WAS A GUN?

28:39.085 --> 28:43.923
- I KNOW WHAT
A GUN IS.

28:43.956 --> 28:44.824
- DID YOU SEE THE GUN,
DETECTIVE?

28:44.857 --> 28:46.926
- IT WAS CHAOTIC,
THEY WERE SCREAMING.

28:46.959 --> 28:48.895
THERE WAS A LITTLE BOY THERE,
IT WAS VERY DARK--

28:48.928 --> 28:49.996
- YES OR NO?

28:50.029 --> 28:52.064
AND I REMIND YOU,
YOU'RE UNDER OATH.

28:52.098 --> 28:53.900
- NO.

28:53.933 --> 28:55.902
I HEARD MY PARTNER YELL,
"GUN."

28:55.935 --> 28:58.437
SO I PULLED MY WEAPON,
AND I HELD IT ON A SUSPECT

28:58.470 --> 28:59.906
WHILE HE RESTRAINED HIM.

28:59.939 --> 29:01.440
YOUR HONOR,
MR. WEDMORE WAS IN CUSTODY.

29:01.473 --> 29:02.909
HE WAS NOT A THREAT.

29:02.942 --> 29:03.910
THE POLICE HAD ALREADY
SECURED THE ROOM.

29:03.943 --> 29:04.977
THEY SHOULD HAVE REQUESTED
A SEARCH WARRANT.

29:05.011 --> 29:08.414
YOUR HONOR, THE DETECTIVE
HAD REASONABLE CAUSE.

29:08.447 --> 29:10.416
THE PLAIN VIEW DOCTRINE
APPLIES HERE.

29:10.449 --> 29:11.918
- PLAIN VIEW? UNDER THE COUCH?
ACROSS THE R--

29:11.951 --> 29:13.920
- MOTION DENIED.

29:13.953 --> 29:15.154
MOVING ON.

29:20.559 --> 29:22.128
- THANKS FOR HAVING MY BACK.
- [sighs]

29:22.161 --> 29:27.399
I CAN'T SAY THAT I SAW
SOMETHING THAT I DIDN'T SEE.

29:27.433 --> 29:30.436
- THAT'S GOOD TO KNOW...
PARTNER.

29:34.006 --> 29:35.307
- WE'VE GOT
THE RIGHT MAN.

29:35.341 --> 29:37.043
- NOT THE RIGHT WAY.

29:37.076 --> 29:41.347
- LOOK, THERE'S
NO BIG CONSPIRACY HERE.

29:41.380 --> 29:42.414
WHAT'S IN THIS
FOR YOU?

29:42.448 --> 29:44.450
- NOTHING, BUT
IF IMPROPRIETIES HAPPEN

29:44.483 --> 29:45.517
ON ORDINARY CASES
LIKE THIS,

